# Main-session skill routing

Use this rule when a message starts with one of:

- `/stage-file-main-session <MASTER_PLAN_RELATIVE_PATH> <STAGE_ID>`
- `/ship-stage-main-session <MASTER_PLAN_RELATIVE_PATH> <STAGE_ID> [--no-resume | --per-task-verify]`

Where `<MASTER_PLAN_RELATIVE_PATH>` is resolved relative to the territory-developer repo root (e.g. `ia/projects/web-platform-master-plan.md`).

## Routing

1. Read the matching wrapper skill file end-to-end:
   - `ia/skills/stage-file-main-session/SKILL.md`
   - `ia/skills/ship-stage-main-session/SKILL.md`
2. Substitute positional args into `{MASTER_PLAN_RELATIVE_PATH}` and `{STAGE_ID}` (and optional flags).
3. Execute the wrapper skill literally, including every **"do not spawn subagents"** / **"do not use the Agent/Task tool"** clause.
4. Do **not** summarize, paraphrase, or condense the skill body — follow it step-by-step.
5. If the wrapper skill file is missing, stop and tell the user which path is missing. Do **not** fall back to the bare `/stage-file` or `/ship-stage` skill silently.

## Flags (ship-stage-main-session only)

Append `--no-resume` or `--per-task-verify` **only** if the user explicitly asked for them in the current turn. Never on your own initiative.

## Relationship to subagent variants

| Variant | Command | Behavior |
|---|---|---|
| Subagent (Claude Code only) | `/stage-file`, `/ship-stage` | Dispatches via Agent/Task tool. |
| Main-session (all agents) | `/stage-file-main-session`, `/ship-stage-main-session` | Executes inline. Works in Cursor Composer-2 and Claude Code without Agent/Task. |

Both variants read the same canonical `ia/skills/stage-file/SKILL.md` / `ia/skills/ship-stage/SKILL.md` — only the execution strategy differs.
